'''Brackish marshes''' develop by [[salt marsh]]es where a significant [[freshwater]] influx dilutes the [[seawater]] to [[brackish]] levels of [[salinity]].  This commonly happens upstream from salt marshes by [[estuaries]] of coastal rivers or near the mouths of coastal rivers with heavy freshwater discharges in the conditions of low [[tidal range]]s.<ref>"Field Guide to Coastal Wetland Plants of the Southeastern United States", by Ralph W. Tiner, [https://books.google.com/books?id=-WYcUxppDo4C&pg=PA15&dq=%22brackish+marshes%22&ei=AMw5SYOEH5uKkASixcngBw#PPA15,M1 p. 15]</ref>

